author: COMSOL
description:
This example models the flow and mass transport in the channels and the gas diffusion layer (GDL) of the oxygen side of a polymer electrolyte fuel cell.

The cathode electrode reaction of the oxygen gas diffusion electrode (GDE) is modeled as an internal boundary condition, where the local current density depends on the overpotential and the local oxygen concentration.

The membrane, anode GDE and anode GDL voltage losses are also included in the model.

The gas stream at the anode side is assumed to be 100% hydrogen, thus excluding the need to model mass and momentum transport at this side of the cell.
